When it did come time for my promotion, they gave me exactly one day to study for their trivia questions, to memorize their favorite song, and to have my uniform looking good. Everyone else I've ever spoken to was given at least a month's notice to accomplish the same. I'm at least grateful that my sponsor informed the board I wouldn't have a clue what they wanted from me when I walked in, so I was thankfully turned around immediately.
